  "text": "To localize sequences in the IEtu1 promoter responsive to KLF4 and KLF15, two deletion mutants were used (Fig. 6A) . The basal promoter activity of IEtu1cat⌬1024 is ϳ4-fold less than IEtu1cat and IEtu1 cat⌬1391 is 25-fold less than IEtu1cat [CITATION_1] . Neuro-2A cells were cotransfected with the designated promoter construct, along with KLF4 or KLF15, and CAT reporter activity was measured at 48 h after transfection. KLF4 activated the fulllength IEtu1 25-fold and IEtu1⌬1024 and IEtu1⌬1391 ϳ50-fold (Fig. 6B) . Although KLF15 transactivated the IEtu1 promoters less efficiently than KLF4, both transcription factors exhibited a similar trend for transactivating the three IEtu1 promoter constructs. IEtu1⌬1391 contains two CACC motifs, two RCRCCYY motifs, one reverse CACC motif, and six reverse RCRCCYY motifs, suggesting these motifs at the distal region of the IEtu1 promoter were not necessary for transactivation by KLF4 or KLF15.",
